    "note": "NEW atomic. The instruments China applied to Japan after the Taiwan-remarks rupture: rare-earth export licensing, travel advisories and the tourism drop, seafood import suspension, visa rules, detained nationals. Dyad gate centroid_ids={ASIA-CHINA} + primary_target=ASIA-JAPAN. Separated from japan_china_taiwan_question because the instrument is orthogonal to the dispute that triggered it and carries its own narrative axis (lawful regulation vs coercion). DELIBERATELY EXCLUDED: 'sales', 'carmaker', 'earnings', 'stocks', 'yen' -- the in-gate corpus has a heavy Toyota/Honda/Nikkei market-noise floor (spec 3, corporate/market class) that is NOT this phenomenon. Overlap with us_china_critical_minerals is 4 titles (it gates on {AMERICAS-USA}). Real-gate audit: 'rare earth' looked 58% foreign against {ASIA-CHINA} alone but is 25/25 on-topic once ASIA-JAPAN gates it; 'seafood' and 'boycott' fall to 0 real hits (the Nordic-salmon noise is gated out) and are KEPT as precise evergreen instruments. DROPPED post-audit: 'detention' -- 4 real hits split between the Dalian story and the embassy 'detention of SDF suspect'; 'detain' (a separate word-start stem, not a prefix of 'detention') covers the phenomenon cleanly at 11/11."
